channel.title: Port forwarding a Belkin Router?
channel.description:
I have a Belkin F5D7230-4 router I set up a static Ip address I went on my routers configuration page and added 43594 to the inbound connection list. This is my first time port forwarding on this router so maybe I am doing something wrong but canyouseeme.org says both ports are closed.
My static ip is 192.168.2.1 On my configuration page it asks for Description - rsps inbound port: 43594-43594 Type: TCP private ip address: 192.168.2.1 private port: 2-2 (I dont know what the provate ports are for.)
I save my changes and check to see if its open and it says connection timed out. I allowed port 43594 through my firewall.
